products.title: Tomato Nadu Premium
products.description: Tomatoes are juicy and sweet, full of antioxidants, and may help fight several diseases and are considered to be a good source of fiber and carbohydrates.

products.title: Asparagus
products.description: Asparagus is a particularly good source of vitamin B6, calcium, magnesium and is particularly low in calories & sodium. Asparagus spears can be eaten cooked or raw!

products.title: Mango Fruit Banganapalli
products.description: Banganapalli or Benishan Mangoes are sourced from Andhra Pradesh. Much larger than the Alphonso, this variant is less fibrous and has a sweet yellow pulp

products.title: Strawberries
products.description: Strawberries belong to the rose family and have over 200 seeds and are known to be rich in vitamins and potassium.

products.title: Papaya
products.description: Papaya is an excellent source of vitamin C and is also packed with fiber, copper, magnesium, potassium, and calcium.

products.title: Blueberry Imported
products.description: Usually grown in the northern hemisphere, Blueberries have been shown in clinical trials to destroy belly fat! This super food show promise in fighting Type II Diabetes, heart disease, dementia and more.

products.title: Banana Yelakki
products.description: Bananas are the new Apples! Power packed with lots of nutrients, they are also an energy booster, antidepressant and helps boost the production of serotonin, a “feel-good hormone.”

products.title: Banana Karpuram
products.description: Karpuram Bananas grow in the states of Tamil Nadu & Kerala. Known to be the sweetest of all banana varieties, this variant is no different from the regular banana providing fibre, typtophan and is known to a natural antacid.

products.title: Broccoli Ooty
products.description: This superfood is touted as one of the healthiest veggies due to its nutritional makeup! It is packed with fiber, antioxidants to fight cancer, and vitamin C to aid in iron absorption. Aim to eat this cruciferous veggie to reap the good-for-you benefits

products.title: Iceberg Lettuce
products.description: Iceberg lettuce is known for having a crisp, crunchy texture and a mildly sweet flavor. They are packed with Vitamins, calcium, iron and is one of the least calorie food you can eat

products.title: Lettuce- Romaine
products.description: Romaine lettuce is sturdy, crunchy, and packed with nutrition and is a hearty salad green. Low in calories, sugar, and carbohydrates and high in vitamins and minerals Known for its nutritional benefits and savory, yet neutral taste.

products.title: Bok Choy
products.description: Bok Choy, also called white Chinese cabbage, belongs to the leafy vegetable pak choi family of Chinese brassicas. Bok Choy has white or green, thick, crunchy stems with light to dark green wide leaves.

products.title: Chinese Cabbage
products.description: Chinese cabbage or Napa cabbage is a great source of soluble and insoluble dietary fiber. It helps build bones, fights fatigue and anemia, helps regulate blood pressure among many benefits

products.title: Celery
products.description: A celebrity favourite! Celery helps lower cholesterol, treats constipation, reduces stress hormone levels, fights inflammation and provides many other benefits.

products.title: Baby Corn Peeled
products.description: Baby corn comes from regular corn that is picked before fertilization. An essential ingredient in Asian and continental cuisine, baby corn contains almost no fat and is low in calories!

products.title: Button Mushroom
products.description: Averaging 2-7 cms, Button Mushrooms have short stems and are mostly white in colour. They have a mild frangrance when cooked. Perfect for stir fry recipes.

products.title: Red Capsicum
products.description: Red capsicums are just green bell peppers that are left to ripe and in fact, are the sweetest in the lot!

products.title: Yellow Capsicum
products.description: Yellow Capsicums are more mature than green ones and have a fruity taste that is milder than red capsicums

products.title: Red Cabbage
products.description: Red Cabbage is high in fiber, making it easier to digest foods and keep your digestive system healthy, and is a good source of vitamins, calcium, magnesium, and zinc, which can help build and maintain healthy bones.

products.title: Bajji Chilli
products.description: Chilli Bajji contains up to seven times the Vitamin C level of an orange and has a range of health benefits, including fighting sinus congestion, aiding digestion and helping to relieve migraines and muscle, joint and nerve pain.

products.title: Green Peas Fresh
products.description: Green Peas are a good source of vitamins C and E, zinc, and other antioxidants that strengthen your immune system.

products.title: Sweet Corn Fresh
products.description: Sweet Corn is dense in carbohydrates and is high in fibre and is rich source of antioxidants and vitamins.

products.title: Onion Big Nasik
products.description: Onions are widely used in a variety of forms and are rich in fiber, which is needed to maintain gut health and bone health.

products.title: Coconut (650 - 700 GMS)
products.description: The coconut palm is one of the most cultivated palms in the world. Apart from the many benefits, coconuts stabilize blood sugar, lower cholestrol and replace blood plasma in an emergency

products.title: Coriander Leaves
products.description: Coriander leaves are delicate looking and have a subtle sweet, earthy aroma. Drinking coriander water everyday is known to help cleanse the stomach.

products.title: Mint Leaves
products.description: Mint leaves are aromatic herbs and are packed with antioxidants, vitamins and have anti-bacterial properties.

products.title: Green Chilli
products.description: Green chillies are loaded with plenty of nutrients like carbohydrates, proteins, fibres, vitamins and minerals

products.title: Carrot Ooty

products.title: Beans Ooty

products.title: Cauliflower
products.description: Belonging to the cabbage family, this vegetable is one where the florets/flowers are consumed. Ut is high in fibre & a good source of anti-oxidants

products.title: Cabbage Cleaned

products.title: Capsicum Green
products.description: The green capsicum is known as bell pepper in other parts of the world. This variety is less sweet than the other varieties of capsicum

products.title: Beetroot
products.description: Beetroots come from the same family as sugar beets but are genetically and nutritionally different. Known for their earthy flavour & aroma, these veggies are versatile and nutitious

products.title: Cucumber
products.description: Cucumbers are known to hydrate the body and skin. Antioxidants in cucumbers can help fight free radicals in your body. Apart from that, putting them on your skin may help ease sunburn pain, swelling, and damaged skin.

products.title: Brinjal Vari
products.description: Perfect for making stuffed Brinjal, this is a small variety with striped purple skin. Brinjals have a Glycemic Index of 15 which is low and hence it is good for diabetics! It is high in fibre, low in sodium and has cancer fighting properties.

products.title: Brinjal Ujala
products.description: This is a medium sized, purple brinjal that has a smooth skin and seedy flesh. Brinjals have a Glycemic Index of 15 which is low and hence it is good for diabetics! It is high in fibre, low in sodium and has cancer fighting properties.

products.title: Brinjal Green
products.description: It has a Glycemic Index of 15 which is low and hence it is good for diabetics! It is high in fibre, low in sodium and has cancer fighting properties. This type is long, green and has a smooth skin.

products.title: Okra (ladies finger)
products.description: Okra is rich in vitamins A and C, as well as antioxidants that help reduce the risk of serious health conditions.

products.title: Pumpkin Red
products.description: Pumpkin Red is low in calories and has 94% water content along with being packed with vitamins and minerals.

products.title: Plantain Stem (Vazhai Thandu)
products.description: Plantain Stem is loaded with an ample amount of fiber and contains a substantial amount of vitamins B6 and potassium.

products.title: Bottlegourd
products.description: Also known as Calabash and is a vine grown for its fruit! Bottle gourds have a light green skin with a white, seedy flesh inside. Known as Lauki in India, consuming the juice of this veggie aids in weight loss & supports in maintaining a healthy heart.

products.title: Sweet Potato
products.description: Sweet potatoes are starchy root vegetables that are rich in fiber, vitamins, and minerals. They’re also high in antioxidants that protect your body from chronic disease.

products.title: Tapioca
products.description: Tapioca contains iron, which is essential to help transport oxygen throughout the body. Tapioca is also very low in sodium.

products.title: Curry Leaves
products.description: Curry leaves are rich in alkaloids, glycosides and phenolic compounds that make this plant a potent health herb.

products.title: Arakeerai
products.description: Arakeerai is nutrient dense and offers a number of health benefits. Rich in protein, minerals and vitamins, it is known to be good for people suffering from diabetes. It is rich in fiber and hence good for digestive health.

products.title: Methi Leaves (Fenugreek)
products.description: Methi leaves are one of the healthiest green leafy vegetables and are rich source of antioxidants, Vitamins
